uk.gov.gchq.palisade.service

Interface Service

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AuditService, CacheService, ConfigurationService, DataService, PalisadeService, PolicyService, ResourceService, UserService
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractLdapUserService, HDFSResourceService, HierarchicalPolicyService, LoggerAuditService, ProxyRestConfigService, ProxyRestDataService, ProxyRestPalisadeService, ProxyRestPolicyService, ProxyRestResourceService, ProxyRestService, ProxyRestUserService, RestConfigServiceV1, RestDataServiceV1, RestPalisadeServiceV1, RestPolicyServiceV1, RestResourceServiceV1, RestUserServiceV1, SimpleCacheService, SimpleConfigService, SimpleDataService, SimplePalisadeService, SimpleUserService

    public interface Service
    This class defines the top level services API.

    The only requirement is that there is a process method, used to process all requests that are passed to a service.

    The applyConfigFrom(ServiceConfiguration) method should implemented so that the class can be configured with an initial configuration.

      • applyConfigFrom

        default void applyConfigFrom(ServiceConfiguration config)
                      throws NoConfigException
        Gives the initial configuration to a service to allow it to configure itself. This method is called by the internal system to configure a service.

        Subclasses should override this implementation which does nothing.

        Subclasses should ONLY throws NoConfigException if a required configuration key is not present

        Parameters:
        config - the configuration
        Throws:
        NoConfigException - if some required element of the configuration is not present

      • recordCurrentConfigTo

        default void recordCurrentConfigTo(ServiceConfiguration config)
        Tells a service to save its configuration to the given configuration object. This method is called by the internal system to save a configuration.

        Subclasses should override this implementation which does nothing.

        Parameters:
        config - the configuration to place initial configuration information into
